nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|In fact, although it sounds counter-intuitive, you actually prefer to balance with a weaker hand than a stronger hand. That is because the points are approximately evenly divided between the 2 sides and the NT opener has most of the points for his side.|
